data.description: Manageable acreage, manageable home – is that not what we all want, a place with room to move about freely and land to enjoy country life but not so big it takes up your entire Saturday to maintain? Here it is! 2.35 acres M/L for you to enjoy as is or add chickens, goat, horse or whatever your heart desires. Gorgeous tree-lined property provides plenty of shade to rest in and enjoy your Louisiana Saturday nights. A peaceful, quiet piece of land here in Welsh, Louisiana with your quaint 2/2 home awaits you. Storage for your yard toys? Available. Shelter for animals? Available. Fruit trees? Available. A 26’ x 26’ two-car carport makes unloading groceries in the rain so much more enjoyable. And if that is not enough parking space, beside the carport is an additional 10’ x 30’ concrete slab for parking more vehicles or your camper. This home offers a split floor plan, utility room with bathroom and kitchen open to dining room. The 4x4 breakfast nook in the kitchen is absolutely adorable! Enough room in the nook to put your breakfast table or your favorite ivy or two. This home sits in Flood Zone X where flood insurance is typically not required. The 26’ x 8’ front porch offers the perfect place to sit and rock in your favorite rocking chair and watch the world go by – enjoy life, it’s shorter than we think. So, call your realtor today to schedule your showing of this precious cottage home and begin your country-life living. All measurements are M/L.
